                <div class="panel-body">
                    Account registration at <strong>MusiGLOBE</strong> is only required if you want to rate songs and get recommendations. Otherwise you could simply visit the website and enjoy listening to songs. 
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTen">How long would it take to respond to a query?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseTen" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    It depends on the category of the query. But members of the admin panel check for customer queries on a daily basis. So we will definitely address it very soon. 
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseEleven">What if the song I want isn't in your database?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseEleven" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    You can reach out to one of our administrators through the query portal and they will add the song to the catalogue as quickly as they can. We are always open to feedback!
                </div>
            </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo">Can I change my rating for a song?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    Sorry, we do not provide that functionality right now. But  we will try to incorporate it soon!
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree">How do I get song recommendations?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    The steps involved in this process are really simple. All you need to do is:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Register an account.</li>
                        <li>Login through your registration ID.</li>
                        <li>Go to the <strong>View Catalogue</strong> section.</li>
                        <li>The next step is to enter the song ID (which would be displayed in the catalogue beside the song name).</li>
                        <li>Rate the song (1-5).</li>
                        <li>The you will have an option to get recommendation.</li>
                        <li>The top '5' recommended songs would be displayed.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFive">How do I remove a song from my playlist?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseFive" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    You can send a query to us through the portal with your registration ID and song you want to remove. We will notify you once the changes are made.
                    <br />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
